Page</a></td></tr></table></form><a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2>Root thread</a><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9840200296759></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9840200296759><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Rogues from a cleric's prospective</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35931><span id=Scholar>Shaladarra</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>23 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 7th 9:53 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a 20th level cleric and a rogue consequently.&nbsp;&nbsp;Today I had a very interesting experience as my cleric grouped with a rogue.<br><br>I know it can be very tempting for rogues to practice safe fall while grouped with a healer, but please don't do it.  It's extremely rude.<br><br>We had just come through a tough fight and I had dropped down to med so I could heal the group.  The next thing I know, the rogue is up on the cliff practicing safe fall doing intentional damage to himself.  Mana to a cleric is precious.  If you have any respect at all for the group cleric, do not try to take advantage of their healing ability by practicing your nifty skills.  Frankly it's a very neat way to end up dead.  I made my mind up when the rogue did this that if it came down to healing him and someone else in a tough spot, he would be the last to get it simply because he inflicted a serious amount of damage on himself (he was down to 2 bulbs).<br><br>For anyone else who has considered doing this or who has done it, please don't.  Clerics, Druids, and Shaman aren't there to heal you while you practice your skills ESPECIALLY when grouped.<br><br>Thanks!   :)<br>&nbsp;<br>Gabriarra Mistmoon - 33 HIE Cleric<br>Shaladarra Sowstorm - 30 Druid<br>Sakarra - 18 Bard <br>Fennin Ro</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
